The article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Donald Trump on October 31, 2020. The memorandum focuses on protecting American jobs, economic opportunities, and national security by supporting innovative technologies for using domestic natural resources, particularly hydraulic fracturing (fracking) and other technologies for extracting natural gas and petroleum. The memorandum emphasizes the importance of these technologies for providing reliable and affordable energy, creating jobs, and reducing energy prices. It directs certain officials to assess the potential economic and trade impacts of banning or restricting the use of these technologies, as well as the national security impacts. The memorandum also reinforces Executive Order 13211, which requires agencies to consider the energy effects of their actions, and provides new guidance for compliance with the order. Overall, the memorandum aims to promote the responsible use of domestic natural resources for the benefit of the American people.